{%- comment -%} ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
    BFC REVIEW FOLLOWUP — Free Expired Film Offer

    Customers who arrive via a Judge.me review-request email and submit
    a review are offered a free roll of expired 35mm film.

    Flow:
      1. Customer clicks "Write a review" in their Judge.me email
      2. URL contains judgeme_token=... — we stash it in sessionStorage
      3. They submit the review (we count 3 Next clicks → product saved)
      4. We watch for Judge.me's modal to disappear from the DOM
      5. Our modal opens with a small form
      6. Form POSTs natively to Base44 (no fetch — sidesteps CORS)
      7. Base44 validates against Shopify orders + checks for duplicates

    No customer pre-fill — Shopify's new Customer Accounts (CAO) system
    keeps `customer` nil in storefront Liquid and blocks /account.json
    with CORS. Users type their email, which Base44 verifies against
    their Shopify order history server-side.

    The "use my default address on file" checkbox is just a flag passed
    to Base44 — when checked, the backend looks up the customer's address
    from Shopify using the verified email.
═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════ {%- endcomment -%}

